{
  "frames": <int>,                     // optional, may be missing
  "map": { ... },                      // optional
  "units": [ ... ],                    // optional (normally present)
  "game_values": { ... },              // optional, usually empty
  "heatmaps": [ ... ],                 // optional
  "logs": [ ... ],                     // recommended
  "upcs": [ ... ],                     // optional
  "tasks": [ ... ],                    // optional
  "trees": [ ... ],                    // optional (decision trees)
  "draw": [ ... ],                     // optional (lines, boxes, circles)
  "debug": { ... }                     // optional
}


To make CherryVis load and display something, you need only:

trace.json.zstd:
{
    "logs": [],
    "game_values": {},
    "heatmaps": []
}

In fact, CherryVis will load even if "logs" is empty—but you need at least these three keys:

✔ Required

logs (array)
game_values (object)
heatmaps (array)

Optional (but safe to include)

frames
units
tasks
upcs

--- Logs ------------------------------------------

{
  "file": "string",     // file path (can be fake)
  "line": 0,            // int
  "frame": 0,           // int
  "message": "string",
  "sev": 0,             // severity: 0=info, 1=warn, 2=error
  "attachments": []     // optional array of { key, value }
}

Only frame and message are truly essential.

"logs": [
    {
      "attachments": [],
      "file": "../src/modules/genericautobuild.cpp",
      "frame": 2,
      "line": 44,
      "message": "Running build zvpohydras",
      "sev": 0
    },
    {
      "attachments": [],
      "file": "../src/modules/upctocommand.cpp",
      "frame": 1694,
      "line": 32,
      "message": "More than one command to unit Friendly i83 Zerg_Drone (483,479) from UPC u2665 (Gather=1) of task No task",
      "sev": 0
    },

